Name: Canadian Pork Loin Chops
Description: Maple-mustard-glazed, lightly-breaded pork chops are spicy and moist and a great Canadian recipe.
Author: WestCoastMom

Name: Sausage Grinder
Description: Cook up a pan of Italian sausages, layer them in hoagie rolls with hot peppers, onions, and cheese for a hearty and satisfying meal.
Author: Allrecipes

Name: Shrimp Tacos
Description: I got the idea for these shrimp tacos from a favorite restaurant. The shrimp is sauteed in honey butter, topped with a delicious mango salsa, and wrapped in a tortilla. It tastes worth a million bucks yet is so simple. Everyone will be begging for more.
Author: abewasabe

Name: Kevin's Teriyaki Chicken
Description: A quick and easy chicken marinade with pineapple, soy sauce, and garlic. Ready in minutes, with the flavor of cooking all day!
Author: Amy Johnson

Name: Aunt Connie's Coconut Cake
Description: With coconut baked into the cake and a generous sprinkle atop a buttery frosting, this decadent white cake is sure to be a family favorite.
Author: Diana

Name: Bunny Pretzels
Description: Refrigerated French bread dough is twisted into bunny pretzels in this adorable appetizer perfect for serving at an Easter egg hunt.
Author: SHORECOOK

Name: Strawberry Rhubarb Custard Pie
Description: The beautiful pairing of strawberries and rhubarb, combined with a smooth custard, creates a mouth-watering and irresistible pie.
Author: Chef John

Name: Roasted Asparagus Salad with Feta Cheese
Description: Roasted asparagus is joined with tomatoes, feta cheese, and lettuce for a salad so flavorful you don't even need dressing.
Author: pbutler

Name: Best of the Best Blueberry Muffins
Description: Big Blueberry muffins with a crusty sugar topping. A recipe I got from my Grandma. The blueberries and the sweet batter are fabulous together. Favorites of all who have tried them. Quick and easy, made with few ingredients. Remember to use paper liners!
Author: AUNTLYNNIE

Name: Chinese Homemade Watercress and Fish Ball Soup
Description: Homemade Chinese watercress and fish ball soup with pork chops, dates, and ginger is simple to prepare and has a wonderful flavor.
Author: hm2006

Name: Risotto Con Radicchio, Gorgonzola, Noci, e Crema di Balsamico
Description: This creamy risotto with radicchio, Gorgonzola cheese, and walnuts is a traditional Italian dish topped with balsamic glaze and Parmigiano.
Author: Buckwheat Queen

Name: Birria de Ameca, Jalisco (Braised Goat)
Description: Goat meat marinated in an ancho chile marinade is slow cooked until tender in this traditional Mexican stew, birria de ameca, for holidays.
Author: HildaM

Name: Chocolate-Peanut Butter Keto Cups
Description: These coconut oil-based chocolate peanut butter cups are a great on-the-go snack when you need to boost your fat intake on the keto diet.
Author: John Larkin

Name: Kiwi-Melon Coolers
Description: Apple juice, frozen kiwi chunks, and frozen honeydew melon are blended together to make these super easy and refreshing kiwi-melon coolers.
Author: CJ

Name: Tropical Mangolicious Smoothie
Description: This is a super simple smoothie with plenty of tropical mango and pineapple flavor, but no added sugar, that you and your kids will love.
Author: ChefDaddy

Name: Quinoa Avocado Kale Bowl with Balsamic Dijon Dressing
Description: Quinoa is layered with kale and avocado in this bright, colorful bowl drizzled with balsamic Dijon dressing and crumbled goat cheese.
Author: tcasa

Name: Frozen Mango Bellini
Description: Mango juice, Prosecco, orange-flavored liqueur, and ice cubes are all you need to make this blended frozen bellini perfect for brunch.
Author: Cocktail Jim

Name: Chicken Quinoa Soup
Description: This protein-filled chicken quinoa soup features carrots, celery, spinach, and bell peppers for amazing color and flavor in one bowl.
Author: riversiderunner

Name: Spicy Black Bean and Quinoa Soup
Description: Quinoa adds plenty of protein to this spicy tomato-based black bean soup that's an easy choice for a family dinner on a busy weeknight.
Author: STTLADY

Name: Split Pea Quinoa Soup
Description: Red quinoa and extra-firm tofu add hearty depth to this easy split pea soup made with fresh vegetables, dried herbs, and chile peppers.
Author: floyd

Name: Ashlei's Smoked Trout Dip
Description: Cream cheese, sour cream, a few seasonings (and of course, smoked trout!) are all you need to make this easy smoked trout dip.
Author: ashlei

Name: Vegan Dill Pasta Salad
Description: Fresh dill, tomatoes, and garbanzo beans star in this easy pasta salad tossed with vegan mayonnaise that's perfect for a summer picnic.
Author: Charley Anderson Hodges

Name: Dutch Crunch Rolls
Description: Fresh homemade rolls are topped with a thick rice flour paste that form a crunchy crust as they bake in this Dutch-inspired recipe.
Author: melody741

Name: Gluten-Free Banana Giraffe Bread
Description: Kids will be excited to see you slice up this gluten-free banana and almond butter bread because it has chocolate spots just like a giraffe.
Author: A Day In the Kitchen

Name: Spinach, Garlic, and Parmesan-Stuffed Pork Roast
Description: A pork roast is stuffed with spinach, garlic, and Parmesan cheese in this easy recipe with a beautiful presentation for dinner parties.
Author: Tonya

Name: Combsie's Ice Cream Lasagna
Description: Ice cream sandwiches are layered with whipped topping, candy pieces, toffee bits, and chocolate syrup in this kid-pleasing dessert lasagna.
Author: BetsyInVT

Name: Tender Tacos al Pastor
Description: Tacos al pastor is a quintessential Mexican dish, with tender pork and pineapple marinated in a savory sauce with orange juice and chiles.
Author: docmancito

Name: Pescado a la Veracruzana (Veracruz-Style Fish)
Description: Fish fillets are baked in a tomato sauce with red bell pepper, capers, and green olives to create this fish dish from Veracruz, Mexico.
Author: Ofelia Bañuelos

Name: Nazook (Sweet Persian Pastry)
Description: These decadent filled cookies made from a rich sour cream dough are a sweet Persian pastry that go wonderfully with tea or coffee.
Author: kaliscook
